+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0173ythEV5yydUYmzPwozE8X","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No checkpoint found. Non-interactive mode: using Autopilot.\n\nThe task is well-specified with a detailed API and behavior specification. The design decisions are essentially already made in the task description. Let me quickly work through the key architectural decisions and then move to implementation.\n\n**Design Decisions (Autopilot):**\n\n1. **File structure**: Single file `src/index.ts` — the implementation is focused enough that splitting would be over-engineering.\n   → Choosing: Single file with clear sections for types, helpers, and the class.\n\n2. **Data model**: Each branch stores a map of document ID → document state (content + version history + deleted flag). Branches track their parent branch and the snapshot point for three-way merge ancestry.\n   → Choosing: Branch stores a deep-cloned snapshot of all documents at creation time, plus subsequent changes.\n\n3. **Three-way merge ancestor tracking**: Store the branch point as a snapshot of document states when the branch was created, serving as the common ancestor for merges.\n   → Choosing: Store ancestor state at branch creation time.\n\n4. **Deep diff for structural merge**: Walk both objects recursively, comparing field-by-field against the base.\n   → Choosing: Recursive object diff with dot-path conflict reporting.\n\nLet me proceed directly to TDD implementation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1192,"cache_read_input_tokens":22937,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1192,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2b1b2eb3-fb34-4700-93d5-0c5e02a2e088","uuid":"650d5b6c-7efe-4582-81c0-a24d4bd541ae"}
